        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 5:48PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
western Pearland, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Western Pearland, eastern Sugar Land, Missouri City, Stafford,
northwestern Manvel, First Colony, Fresno, Meadows Place, Arcola,
Iowa Colony, Thompsons, Sienna, Fifth Street, Riverstone, Fort Bend
Houston, South Acres / Crestmont Park, Fondren Gardens, Central
Southwest, Brays Oaks, and Westbury.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
